column17: Spanish interest in the area was fading\
column18: and Quadra was eventually removed from the island's name.\\"\

column16: \\"story\\": \\"Dubbed the \\\\\\"Father of British Columbia\\\\\\" James Douglas was the first Governor of the Colony of British Columbia. He also governed The Colony of Vancouver Island from 1851-1864. Douglas resided in Fort Victoria until 1851 when he built a home overlooking James Bay where the RBCM now stands. In 1852 Douglas purchased 500 acres of HBC land from Fort Street to the coast where present day Rockland and Fairfield exist.\\"\
